<subSubSection id="C33017F2FFC0FFDDFF1AFABDFE42C3EB" pageId="1" pageNumber="90" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8B954479FFC0FFDDFF1AFABDFED0C0CB" blockId="1.[136,1452,844,1697]" pageId="1" pageNumber="90">
<emphasis id="B95E986BFFC0FFDDFF1AFABDFEC2C017" bold="true" box="[189,294,1348,1373]" pageId="1" pageNumber="90">Ecology:</emphasis>
—Along roads in shaded mixed evergreen forest; elevation 
<quantity id="4CD2E99CFFC0FFDDFC6CFABDFBB8C017" box="[971,1116,1348,1373]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="90" unit="m" value="850.0" valueMax="1000.0" valueMin="700.0">700–1000 m</quantity>
. Flowering in February, May, fruiting in July.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B954479FFC0FFDDFF1AFA75FE29C0EF" blockId="1.[136,1452,844,1697]" box="[189,461,1420,1445]" pageId="1" pageNumber="90">
<emphasis id="B95E986BFFC0FFDDFF1AFA75FEA3C0EF" bold="true" box="[189,327,1420,1445]" pageId="1" pageNumber="90">Thai name:</emphasis>
—Me hang.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B954479FFC0FFDDFF1AFA49FF00C37F" blockId="1.[136,1452,844,1697]" pageId="1" pageNumber="90">
<emphasis id="B95E986BFFC0FFDDFF1AFA49FEEDC083" bold="true" box="[189,265,1456,1481]" pageId="1" pageNumber="90">Notes:</emphasis>
—This species was not included by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB3988FFC0FFDDFD05FA49FCD2C083" author="Craib, W. G." box="[674,822,1456,1481]" pageId="1" pageNumber="90" pagination="563 - 809" refId="ref2154" refString="Craib, W. G. (1931) Flora Siamensis Enumeratio 1 (4). Siam Society, Bangkok, pp. 563 - 809." type="book chapter" year="1931">Craib (1931)</bibRefCitation>
. It is similar to the Indochinese 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A3FFAFFC0FFDDFB07FA49FEBDC0A7" authority="Merrill (1938: 32)" authorityName="Merrill" authorityPageNumber="32" authorityYear="1938" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Escalloniaceae" genus="Polyosma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Escalloniales" pageId="1" pageNumber="90" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dolichocarpa">
<emphasis id="B95E986BFFC0FFDDFB07FA49FA4FC083" box="[1184,1451,1456,1481]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="90">Polyosma dolichocarpa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB3988FFC0FFDDFF2FFA2DFEBDC0A7" author="Merrill, E. D." box="[136,345,1492,1517]" pageId="1" pageNumber="90" pagination="21 - 70" refId="ref2182" refString="Merrill, E. D. (1938) New or noteworthy Indo-Chinese plants. Journal of the Arnold Arboretum 19: 21 - 70." type="journal article" year="1938">Merrill (1938: 32)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, described from 
<collectingCountry id="F33D04E9FFC0FFDDFDB1FA2DFD9DC0A7" box="[534,633,1492,1517]" name="Vietnam" pageId="1" pageNumber="90">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
. Both taxa are the only ones in SE Asia with a long-pilose indumentum. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A3FFAFFC0FFDDFF2FFA01FE73C35B" authorityName="Merrill" authorityYear="1938" box="[136,407,1528,1553]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Escalloniaceae" genus="Polyosma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Escalloniales" pageId="1" pageNumber="90" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dolichocarpa">
<emphasis id="B95E986BFFC0FFDDFF2FFA01FE73C35B" box="[136,407,1528,1553]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="90">Polyosma dolichocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs however sufficiently in distinctly sulcate fruits and longer (
<quantity id="4CD2E99CFFC0FFDDFB11FA01FAFEC35B" box="[1206,1306,1528,1553]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="90" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3 mm</quantity>
) pedicels in flowers.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B954479FFC0FFDDFF1AF9B9FE42C3EB" blockId="1.[136,1452,844,1697]" pageId="1" pageNumber="90">
Schulze-Menz annotated specimens of this new species as 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A3FFAFFC0FFDDFC26F9B9FB70C313" box="[897,1172,1600,1625]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Escalloniaceae" genus="Polyosma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Escalloniales" pageId="1" pageNumber="90" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dolichotricha">
<emphasis id="B95E986BFFC0FFDDFC26F9B9FB70C313" box="[897,1172,1600,1625]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="90">Polyosma dolichotricha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a name that remained unpublished like so many other names he suggested. But to prevent possible confusion with 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A3FFAFFC0FFDDFB33F99DFAA1C337" authorityName="Merrill" authorityYear="1938" box="[1172,1349,1636,1661]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Escalloniaceae" genus="Polyosma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Escalloniales" pageId="1" pageNumber="90" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dolichocarpa">
<emphasis id="B95E986BFFC0FFDDFB33F99DFAA1C337" box="[1172,1349,1636,1661]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="90">P. dolichocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we here propose a different name.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
