<emphasis id="B95E986BFFC0FFDDFF2FF851FF2DC28B" bold="true" box="[136,201,1960,1985]" pageId="1" pageNumber="90">Note:</emphasis>
—The thin leaves and the smooth fruits with oblique base are typical for 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A3FFAFFC0FFDDFC51F851FB97C28B" authorityName="Bennett" authorityYear="1840" box="[1014,1139,1960,1985]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Escalloniaceae" genus="Polyosma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Escalloniales" pageId="1" pageNumber="90" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wallichii">
<emphasis id="B95E986BFFC0FFDDFC51F851FB97C28B" box="[1014,1139,1960,1985]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="90">P. wallichii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The Thai plants (with soon glabrescent leaves with appressed hairs) differ slightly from collections from 
<collectingCountry id="F33D04E9FFC0FFDDFC42F835FBC5C2AF" box="[997,1057,1996,2021]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="90">India</collectingCountry>
, 
